1 Download debian bookworm which is still have 32 bit https://cdimage.debian.org/mirror/cdimage/archive/12.1.0/i386/iso-cd/
2 Setup debian 13 32 bit
3 When running tasksel do not select gnome and debian desktop environment or other desktop environment that listed on tasksel because its heavy just standard system utility only instead
4 After install run login as root first then apt install sudo then nano /etc/sudoers then add yourusername  ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL then ctrl x y enter
5 Exit root then login as yourusername
6 Run sudo apt install links then links https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Ubuntu-32 then find ubuntu-logo-text.png then name it to ubuntu-logo-text.png and find ubuntu-logo-text-dark.png then name it to ubuntu-logo-text=dark.png
7 then ls then sudo mv /home/yourusername/ubuntu-logo-text.png /usr/share/pixmaps then sudo mv /home/yourusername/ubuntu-logo-text-dark.png /usr/share/pixmaps
8 then sudo nano /etc/os-release
then change

PRETTY_NAME="Debian GNU/Linux 12 (bookworm)"
NAME="Debian GNU/Linux"
VERSION_ID="12"
VERSION="12 (bookworm)"
VERSION_CODENAME=bookworm
ID=debian
and its HOME_URL SUPPORT_URL And BUG_REPORT_URL

To

