Then sudo apt-mark hold base-files
Then sudo apt-mark hold desktop-base
Then sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

9 Then run sudo nano ~/.config/neofetch/config.conf

Locate the ASCII section by searching for the line starting with ascii_distro (usually set to "auto").
Update the value to "ubuntu"

ascii_distro="ubuntu"

then ctrl x y enter

10 Run sudo nano /etc/issue then change Debian GNU/Linux 12 \n \1 To Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS \n \l

Run sudo nano /etc/issue.net then change Debian GNU/Linux 12 to Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS

Run sudo rm /etc/motd then sudo reboot

11 Then sudo nano /etc/default/grub then change GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR To GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Ubuntu" Then Change GRUB_TIMEOUT=5 To GRUB_TIMEOUT=0

Then sudo update-grub
